al sinus","Cloacal membrane"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Egenital tubercle\u003C/strong\u003E is a midline embryonic structure that develops into either the clitoris or penis depending on androgen exposure. In the absence of testosterone and dihydrotestosterone (DHT), the genital tubercle develops into the clitoris by default.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eurethral folds\u003C/strong\u003E develop into the labia minora in females, whilst the \u003Cstrong\u003Elabioscrotal swelling\u003C/strong\u003E develops into the labia majora in females. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eurogenital sinus\u003C/strong\u003E gives rise to the lower portion of the vagina and urethra, and the \u003Cstrong\u003Ecloacal membrane\u003C/strong\u003E breaks down to form the anal and urogenital openings. This sexual differentiation occurs between weeks 9-12 of embryonic development. The presence of testosterone and DHT would cause the genital tubercle to elongate and develop into the penis instead.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The genital tubercle develops into either the clitoris or penis depending on the presence of androgens during embryonic development.","In the absence of testosterone and dihydrotestosterone, the genital tubercle develops into the clitoris by default.","Sexual differentiation of external genitalia occurs between weeks 9-12 of embryonic development."],"references":["Baskin L, Shen J, Sinclair A, Cao M, Liu X, Liu G, Isaacson D, Overland M, Li Y, Cunha GR. Development of the human penis and clitoris. Differentiation. 2018 Sep-Oct;103:74-85. doi: 10.1016/j.diff.2018.08.001. Epub 2018 Aug 23. PMID: 30249413; PMCID: PMC6234061.","Cunha GR, Baskin LS. Development of the external genitalia. Differentiation. 2020 Mar-Apr;112:7-9. doi: 10.1016/j.diff.2019.10.008. Epub 2019 Dec 4. PMID: 31881402; PMCID: PMC7138693.","P A A, Arbor TC, Krishan K. Embryology, Sexual Development. [Updated 2023 Aug 28]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK557601/","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96308"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16124"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96308","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96308"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-15T14:54:37+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-15T14:54:47+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8815"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114308"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4934","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4934"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf46","name":"Reproduc